Job Title: Lead DevOps Platform Engineer – Kubernetes Focus
Location: [Insert Location or Remote]
Job Type: Full-Time
About the Role:
We are seeking a highly skilled Lead DevOps Engineer to drive and scale our infrastructure, with a primary focus on Kubernetes orchestration and cloud-native technologies. In this leadership role, you will architect, implement, and manage our containerized environments, ensuring performance, security, and reliability for critical applications and services.
Key Responsibilities:
•	Lead the design, implementation, and maintenance of scalable Kubernetes-based infrastructure.
•	Architect and manage CI/CD pipelines that enable automated testing, deployment, and monitoring of microservices.
•	Define and enforce best practices for containerization, infrastructure as code (IaC), and Kubernetes operations.
•	Collaborate with development, security, and operations teams to build resilient and secure cloud-native solutions.
•	Drive improvements in observability, including logging, metrics, and alerting using tools like Prometheus, Data Dog, or similar.
•	Manage and mentor a team of DevOps engineers, ensuring technical growth and consistent delivery.
•	Own and maintain Helm charts, Kubernetes manifests, and automation scripts for multi-environment deployments.
•	Troubleshoot and resolve complex issues in cloud and containerized environments.
•	Stay up to date with industry trends, tools, and Kubernetes CNCF ecosystem advancements.
Required Qualifications:
•	7+ years of experience in DevOps, Site Reliability Engineering, or Infrastructure Engineering.
•	4+ years of hands-on Kubernetes experience in a production-grade environment (EKS, GKE, AKS, or self-managed clusters).
•	Deep knowledge of Docker, Helm, and Kubernetes components (e.g., controllers, CRDs, networking, RBAC).
•	Strong proficiency with Infrastructure as Code tools (Terraform, Anisble or similar).
•	Expertise in CI/CD tools like Jenkins, GitHub Actions, Azure DevOps, or GitLab CI.
•	Proficient in scripting and automation (Python, Bash, Powershell).
•	Experience with cloud platforms such as AWS, Azure, or GCP.
•	Familiarity with service mesh (e.g., Istio or Linkerd) and Kubernetes security best practices.
•	Strong problem-solving skills and ability to work independently and in a team.
•	Excellent communication and collaboration skills.
Preferred Qualifications:
•	Certified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA) or Certified Kubernetes Application Developer (CKAD).
•	Certified in Azure, Azure ADO, Azure Architecure, Azure DevOps, Azure security practices
•	Experience managing high-availability, multi-region clusters.
•	Background in monitoring, logging, and incident response processes.
•	Experience with GitOps tools like Argo CD or Flux.
Why Join Us:
•	Work on cutting-edge cloud-native technologies with real impact.
•	Be part of a collaborative, forward-thinking team.
•	Competitive compensation and benefits.
•	Opportunities for growth, certifications, and leadership development.


